Source: pg-savior
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/viggy28/pg_savior

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-savior
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-savior
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Prevent accidental data loss and risky schema changes
  pg_savior installs PostgreSQL hooks that block risky DML and DDL before
  they run, including DELETE or UPDATE without a WHERE clause, large
  estimated row changes, CREATE INDEX without CONCURRENTLY, unsafe ALTER
  TABLE operations, TRUNCATE or DROP TABLE on large tables, and DROP
  DATABASE. The hook must be loaded through shared_preload_libraries,
  session_preload_libraries, or LOAD before CREATE EXTENSION registers the
  SQL objects in each database. For maintenance DDL such as installing other
  extensions, use pg_savior.bypass in that session or load pg_savior after
  those objects are installed.
